CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 14, 1958, pg. B6, reads: "DOCTOR OF PHILOSOPHY - Twenty-six year old Donald Alvin Tunie of 1300 Glenn St., Homestead, son of Rev. and Mrs. E. P. Tunie of Clark Memorial Baptist Church, Homestead, received his Doctor of Philosophy Degree, upon completion of a major study in Spanish"
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Donald Alvin Tunie wearing eyeglasses and doctoral gown, after receiving Doctor of Philosophy Degree, at University of Pittsburgh graduation
